FEATURE DESCRIPTIONS
--------------------
thalach: Maximum heart rate achieved
oldpeak: ST depression induced by exercise
cp: Chest pain type (0-3)
ca: Number of major vessels colored by fluoroscopy
exang: Exercise induced angina
slope: Slope of peak exercise ST segment
thal: Thalassemia test result

MODEL INTERPRETATION
--------------------
The model correctly predicts:
- 87% of all cases overall
- 89% of actual disease cases (good for screening)
- 87% of healthy cases (good for avoiding unnecessary tests)

STRENGTHS
---------
1. Good balance between precision and recall
2. Uses routine clinical measurements
3. Easy to interpret feature importance
4. Low overfitting (train/test scores similar)

LIMITATIONS
-----------
1. Moderate dataset size
2. Single geographic location data
3. No time-series information
4. Binary classification only

